{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Spen Taylor","author":"Spen Taylor"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"333575fd-9c8b-5263-9d8d-22882425d95b","excerpt":"MotivationI wanted a platform that would allow for more passive strategies that could create and track multiple smaller trades within the same market but only…","html":"<h2>Motivation</h2>\n<p>I wanted a platform that would allow for more passive strategies that could create and track multiple smaller trades within the same market but only found platforms that would give advice to either sell or buy.\nWhen I say ‘passive’ I mean that the strategy can be run once or twice a day, without the requirement of constantly running. An example would be to open 5 trades on the sell side at increments of 10%. We might only run our strategy once a day, so these open orders can sit there and fill in between and the strategy can just respond the next time it runs, rather than selling once and missing out on price action.</p>\n<h2>Back-testing</h2>\n<p>To test a strategy, users can select a data set and run their strategy over the price sequence.\nAs the back-tester runs through the data set it executes the strategy logic and handles any ‘advice’ given by the logic - calculating new balances and creating &#x26; closing orders.\nThe results that this back-tester gives are unrealistically optimistic in that they don’t factor in fees or account for the effect real trading would have on the market (however small) - so ignores the inevitable slippages that would normally effect the end result.</p>\n<h2>Live ‘Paper’ Trading</h2>\n<p>As with the back-tester, users can configure their strategy and run it against live price data.\nThe data comes from the coinbase-pro API and each incoming tick runs through the same mechanism as the back-tester (for the sake of consistency between the two).\nIn practice I found this less useful than back-testing simply because the back-testing covers so much time data almost instantly.</p>\n<h3>Data Sets</h3>\n<p>I created a script to scrape historic data from CoinGecko for use in the back-tester, allowing users a wide selection of price histories to back-test their strategies against:\n\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/3e9f440675dbd5c89c90b9494f70541d/5d571/historic-data.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin: 7vw 0; max-width: 1360px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 33.33333333333333%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <picture>\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/3e9f440675dbd5c89c90b9494f70541d/53e9f/historic-data.webp 340w,\n/static/3e9f440675dbd5c89c90b9494f70541d/0991f/historic-data.webp 680w,\n/static/3e9f440675dbd5c89c90b9494f70541d/9d77c/historic-data.webp 1360w,\n/static/3e9f440675dbd5c89c90b9494f70541d/28e69/historic-data.webp 1842w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 1360px) 100vw, 1360px\"\n          type=\"image/webp\"\n        />\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/3e9f440675dbd5c89c90b9494f70541d/a2595/historic-data.png 340w,\n/static/3e9f440675dbd5c89c90b9494f70541d/2473e/historic-data.png 680w,\n/static/3e9f440675dbd5c89c90b9494f70541d/55534/historic-data.png 1360w,\n/static/3e9f440675dbd5c89c90b9494f70541d/5d571/historic-data.png 1842w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 1360px) 100vw, 1360px\"\n          type=\"image/png\"\n        />\n        <img\n          class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n          style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n          src=\"/static/3e9f440675dbd5c89c90b9494f70541d/55534/historic-data.png\"\n          alt=\"historic data screenshot\"\n          title=\"\"\n          src=\"/static/3e9f440675dbd5c89c90b9494f70541d/55534/historic-data.png\"\n        />\n      </picture>\n      </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    \nI also built a generator to get random new chart shapes to try out (though it’s not particularly sophisticated):\n\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/5317052300f832e1150641a374857235/2b918/generate-data.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin: 7vw 0; max-width: 1360px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 66.22222222222223%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <picture>\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/5317052300f832e1150641a374857235/53e9f/generate-data.webp 340w,\n/static/5317052300f832e1150641a374857235/0991f/generate-data.webp 680w,\n/static/5317052300f832e1150641a374857235/9d77c/generate-data.webp 1360w,\n/static/5317052300f832e1150641a374857235/049fa/generate-data.webp 1800w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 1360px) 100vw, 1360px\"\n          type=\"image/webp\"\n        />\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/5317052300f832e1150641a374857235/a2595/generate-data.png 340w,\n/static/5317052300f832e1150641a374857235/2473e/generate-data.png 680w,\n/static/5317052300f832e1150641a374857235/55534/generate-data.png 1360w,\n/static/5317052300f832e1150641a374857235/2b918/generate-data.png 1800w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 1360px) 100vw, 1360px\"\n          type=\"image/png\"\n        />\n        <img\n          class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n          style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n          src=\"/static/5317052300f832e1150641a374857235/55534/generate-data.png\"\n          alt=\"generate data screenshot\"\n          title=\"\"\n          src=\"/static/5317052300f832e1150641a374857235/55534/generate-data.png\"\n        />\n      </picture>\n      </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<h2>Tick Cycle</h2>\n<p>To</p>\n<p>One of the key goals I had in mind while designing the runner was to allow the user to write a minimum amount of code in their strategies. Here’s what I did to achieve this:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Created a cycle of: <code class=\"language-text\">processLastTick</code> > <code class=\"language-text\">calculateCurrentTick</code> > <code class=\"language-text\">processCurrentTick</code> to handle any common work</li>\n<li>Created a dynamic form, built from the form field schema and default values given by the strategy</li>\n</ul>","frontmatter":{"title":"Crypto Bot Runner","date":"May 06, 2015","description":"A platform for building, testing and running trading algorithms using historic and live data.","thumbnail":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","aspectRatio":1.7729672650475186,"src":"/static/e1a8aa26fb737c735a154ed399383767/41d74/backtest-2.png","srcSet":"/static/e1a8aa26fb737c735a154ed399383767/fa754/backtest-2.png 340w,\n/static/e1a8aa26fb737c735a154ed399383767/1bf7a/backtest-2.png 680w,\n/static/e1a8aa26fb737c735a154ed399383767/41d74/backtest-2.png 1360w,\n/static/e1a8aa26fb737c735a154ed399383767/5bd11/backtest-2.png 2040w,\n/static/e1a8aa26fb737c735a154ed399383767/31030/backtest-2.png 2720w,\n/static/e1a8aa26fb737c735a154ed399383767/13946/backtest-2.png 3358w","sizes":"(max-width: 1360px) 100vw, 1360px"}}}}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"slug":"/crypto-bot-runner/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/burberry/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Burberry"}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/wordpress/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"